itemDescription: British Royal Air Force fighter pilot

wikipedia_page.main: Wing Commander Edward Chatham Wolfe  (11 June 1911 – 19 April 1994) was a famed World War II Royal Air Force fighter pilot who flew during the Battle of Britain.

response: * Edward Wolfe (1685–1759) was a British Army officer.
* Edward Wolfe (RAF officer) (1911–1994), Battle of Britain pilot
* Edward Wolfe (artist) RA (1897–1982), South African-born artist who worked with Roger Fry
